<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/everquest/cgi-bin/postings.cgi?action=newtopic&amp;number=1&amp;forum=Developer|APO|s+Corner&amp;DaysPrune=20&amp;LastLogin=">Have your Say</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
So I am assuming that by the very fact I placed class related issues and Warrior on this message it will be ignored...but I need to tell someone at verrant to help us warriors so here goes. <br>
<br>
First off, I am frustrated so some of this may come off like a rant (it prolly is to some extent) but really I am trying to explain my frustration and how you could fix it...Trust me I am not alone, I know you guys read the Bard bard...Have you been to THE Warrior board? I dont think so, try it .. you might like it www.thesteelwarrior.com .  Here is goes:<br>
<br>
Warriors are the most broken class in EQ history.  The concept of a warrior is what?  What is a warrior supposed to be good at?  What skills and abilities make a warrior unique or special over other classes?  These are not rhetorical questions, I would love real answers to these questions, honnest answers.<br>
<br>
Forgive me if I am wrong but I do not believe that a single developer or designer that currently works for EQ today has played or plays on a regular basis a warrior.  I can tell because if one of your people did they would be writing this instead of me.  <br>
<br>
Imagine my suprise as I began playing a warrior finding out I am not the master of damage, or defense, or anything.  I have taunt...but a ranger with a low level spell can pull aggro from me and with his spells do more damage fight longer and in general be more effective in everything warrior...and now with planar AA?  He now gets the one thing we had he didn't Criticals!  Thanks EQ, on that move.<br>
<br>
I am part of the only class COMPLETELY dependant on the equipment I have...not spells, not skills, nothing just equipment.<br>
<br>
Warriors can solo to 50...even 60 (did you know that....do you have anyone in the office who has?...without Verrant buffs or twinking?)  Do you wanna know what doing that is like?  Killing the same mob over and over until you're blind because it may be the only safe mob at your level?  We can group to 60 too but here is the thing...rather than controling the situation...leading the charge as it were, we need to make sure everyone else does not out damage us..the freaking warrior needs to beg the dagger wielding rogue and the prancing  monk &quot;please sir can you not hit so much?  I can't keep aggro.&quot; <br>
<br>
There is nothing like watching a monk get whacked and take less damage than I do.  I am in magical plate armor...how can I get some magic pjs like the monks wear that mitigatse all that damage?  Rather than avoiding it?<br>
<br>
Now what was that famous ratio you guys tried to convince us you were implementing during melee balancing? 0.8 1 1.2 ?  or something like that?<br>
<br>
Have you even done real parseing on DPS by actual players?  According to our measures we are seeing rediculous ratios 1.5 or even 2.0 times as much damage as warriors.  Hmmm it seems that you guys again need to spend some time as a warrior and find out what real tanking is all about.<br>
<br>
Really I don't believe you guys have spent any time as a warrior at all, a bard , druid , pally, ranger,  what ever, for those nifty spell effects walk a mile in my shoes and see. <br>
<br>
I AM A WARRIOR <p>Ragtooth Irongrip <br>
40 Warrior <br>
The Guard<br>
